      <section eId="sec_13_4_26">
        <num>13-4-26</num>
        <content>
          <p>If the promise of a party is to deliver on demand, the demand must be reasonable as to time, place, and manner; if the promise is to deliver at a certain time and place, a tender at the time and place is effective though the receiver is not present.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 2817; Code 1868, § 2825; Code 1873, § 2876; Code 1882, § 2876; Civil Code 1895, § 3730; Civil Code 1910, § 4324; Code 1933, § 20-1107.)</p>
        </content>
